Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
deleteSdpObject(25.10)                                  deleteSdpObject(25.10)

Name
       deleteSdpObject

Syntax
        deleteSdpObject

       [-help]

       {-object   <object_name_list>   [-keepCellPlacement   ]   |   -obstruct
       <group_name_list> | -emptyRow <instance_name> [-numRow <value>]}

       Deletes one of the following:

              * SDP group(s) or element(s)

              * A  placement  blockage  associated  with  the  specified   SDP
                group(s)

              * Empty row(s) adjacent to the specified instance

       Use  the  deleteSdpObject  command to modify structure of existing data
       path(s) easily and to remove existing SDP groups or elements.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes type and  default  in-
              formation for each deleteSdpObject parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command: man deleteSdpObject.

       -emptyRow  <instance_name>
              Deletes  the  empty  row(s)  adjacent  to the specified instance
              based on the justifyBy constraint of the group to which the  in-
              stance  belongs.  If  the group is justified by SW/SE, the empty
              rows below the specified instance are deleted. If the  group  is
              justified  by NW/NE, the empty rows above the specified instance
              are deleted.

              Note:  If the rows adjacent to the specified instances  are  not
              empty, an error message is returned.

       -keepCellPlacement
              Preserves  the  cell  placement of remaining SDP members when an
              SDP object is deleted.  If  this  parameter  is  not  specified,
              deleteSdpObject  unplaces  all  SDP  members  while deleting the
              specified SDPs. This option can be used only with  -object.

       -numRow <value>
              Indicates the number of empty rows to be deleted.

              Note:  If this parameter is not  specified,  one  empty  row  is
              deleted by default.

       -object <object_name_list>
              Deletes  the  specified  SDP  group  or instance. If you want to
              delete more than one object, enclose the object names in {}.

       -obstruct  <group_name_list>
              Deletes the placement blockage over the specified SDP group(s).

Examples
              * The following command deletes the SDP group TestGrp.

                deleteSdpObject -object TestGrp

              * The following command deletes a placement  blockage  over  the
                SDP group sdpGrp1.

                deleteSdpObject -obstruct sdpGrp1

              * The  following  command  deletes  two  empty  rows  below  the
                DTMF_INST/ROM_512x16_0_INST instance where the group to  which
                ROM_512x16_0_INST belongs has justifyBy constraint set as SW.

                deleteSdpObject  -emptyRow DTMF_INST/ROM_512x16_0_INST -numRow
                2

